International Brief -- Showa Aluminum Corp.:
   Pretax Profit Climbs 5.5%;
   Further Gain Is Forecast
For the current fiscal year, ending Nov. 30, 1992, Showa
expects its consolidated pretax profit will rise to 7.70
billion yen. Net income is pegged at 3.30 billion yen, with
sales at 187.80 billion yen on a consolidated basis.
   The pretax profit represents operating profit plus
non-operating profit including financial income and expenses.
The net income represents pretax profit plus extraordinary
gains or losses and tax payments.
   Unconsolidated results are those of the parent alone.
Consolidated results include those of subsidiaries.